        <releasenotes>
            <![CDATA[
            <h3>Version 2.0.25 - Prioritize "l" Field for Current Position</h3>

            <h4>Bug Fix</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Prioritize "l" field over "resume" when extracting slide position</li>
                <li>"l" field = ACTUAL current position (0-indexed)</li>
                <li>"resume" field = FURTHEST progress (now fallback only)</li>
                <li>Fixes incorrect position when user navigates backward</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Technical Details</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Updated extractSlideFromParsedData() with priority check</li>
                <li>Updated extractSlideFromText() with "l" field regex</li>
                <li>Converts 0-indexed "l" to 1-indexed slide number</li>
                <li>Added clarifying comments about field semantics</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Previous Versions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>v2.0.24: Unlimited intercepts within 10s window</li>
                <li>v2.0.23: Skip suspend_data tracking during intercept</li>
                <li>v2.0.22: Re-enable write interception (l field only)</li>
                <li>v2.0.16: URL-based slide navigation (?slide=X) for embed</li>
            </ul>
            ]]>
